The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 21: Gail (India) Ltd has signed a memorandum of understanding with Business Development Corp Ltd (BDCL) of Bangladesh for a joint initiative in gas transmission, pipelines and distribution networks in the neighbouring country. The MoU was signed by Gail director B. S. Negi and BDCL group vice-president A. K. M. Ruhul Amin, the domestic gas major stated in a release. The duo will jointly identify exploration and production opportunities in Bangladesh.

 New Delhi, March 21: EID Parry India today said it has approved the splitting of shares. The board of directors has decided to split the stock from Rs 10 per share to Rs 2 per share subject to shareholders? approval through a postal ballot, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 New Delhi, March 21: The department of telecom would meet the CMDs of BSNL, MTNL and consultants on March 23 to discuss the process of synergising the operations of the two state-owned telecom majors.

 New Delhi, March 21: UTI Bank has raised a total of $239.30 million through its global depository receipts issue, which was admitted for trading on the London Stock Exchange today.

 Dubai, March 21: Oman Air is planning to expand its network in India with new services to Delhi and Hyderabad. It would also enhance its capacity on Mumbai and Kochi routes.

 New Delhi, March 21: ONGC is planning to set up a Rs 4000-crore refinery in Barmer in Rajasthan where Cairn Energy of the UK has made recent oil discoveries. ?We are talking to Cairn Energy to jointly set up the refinery,? said ONGC chairman Subir Raha.

 Mumbai, March 21: National Mineral Development Corporation (NMDC) is planning to invest Rs 1,000 crore over the next three years for exploring new mines of 20 to 30 million tonne capacity.




